aVNow, 95 percent of the guys that I was locked up with
p20
aVhad been drug dealers on the outside,
p21
aVbut when they talked about what they did,
p22
aVthey talked about it in a different jargon,
p23
aVbut the business concepts that they talked about
p24
aVweren't unlike those that you'd learn in a first year MBA class at Wharton:
p25
aVpromotional incentives, you never charge a first-time user,
p26
aVfocus-grouping new product launches,
p27
aVterritorial expansion.
